  "coarse_graining": {
    "description": "The macroscopic n\u0304 in the RAR counts gravitational modes, not individual bosons. Within one healing length \u03be = \u221a(GM/g\u2020), all bosons occupy a single collective mode (the soliton ground state). The number of independent modes scales as (R/\u03be)\u00b3. The gravitational n\u0304 is NOT N_occ (which counts bosons per de Broglie volume), but rather the ratio of actual DM density to the critical density for one boson per mode at the gravitational coarse-graining scale. This is why n\u0304 ~ 1-30 rather than ~10\u2079\u00b3.",
    "key_relation": "n\u0304_grav \u2248 \u03c1_DM(r) \u00d7 \u03be\u00b3 / M_mode, where M_mode = \u03c1_crit \u00d7 \u03be\u00b3",
